<p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0=
 1em 0;"><strong>A bubble &#8211; too many good solutions swarming the obvi=
ous problems &#8211; is far more likely than the problem not getting solved=
!&nbsp;</strong></p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-heigh=
t: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Not to be gross, but a swarm&#8217;s success i=
n solving a problem that it&#8217;s identified is as inevitable as those vi=
deos in which swarms of ants eat food, like this:&nbsp;</p><a href=3D"https=
://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEtvhSAQhX-NLA3y8LFg0aS56bLbrgzCXCVVMDBc478=
vXhdNyJDM5MyZ8xmNMId4qj0kJFcZ8dxBeTjSCogQSU4QR2dV07KeSzEQq4RtetkTl8ZnBNi0Wx=
