ght could also be seen as <strong>front-running the swarm</strong>.</p><p s=
tyle=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em=
 0;">SpaceX has likely secured the biggest prize in this space tech cycle, =
as it should for its counterintuitive contributions to the category. More i=
mportantly from the perspective of progress, it <strong>opened up the categ=
ory to the swarm</strong>.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">SpaceX has made the economics =
of space technology more favorable, and it&#8217;s also amplified other phe=
romones for space tech. Space is <strong>sexier</strong> now, the <strong>T=
AM</strong> looks bigger, <strong>barriers</strong> are lower, it&#8217;s m=
ore <strong>visible</strong>, and potential outcomes are bigger. It kicked =
off a <strong>renaissance</strong> in space exploration and commercializati=
on.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px=
; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Elon been so successful in making space commercially =
viable that there are bubbles in certain sub-categories of space tech now. =
From humanity&#8217;s perspective, <strong>that&#8217;s a phenomenal thing<=
/strong>. Talent and capital is swarming problems whose solutions might mea=
n multi-planetary life, access to cheaper energy sources, and new frontiers=
 that allow humanity to continue to <strong>grow</strong>.</p><p style=3D"c=
olor: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Spac=
eX did the near-impossible over the course of two decades in order to final=
ly <strong>attract the swarm</strong>, which will now aid in the effort to =
open up space.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-h=
eight: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">So Elon hacked the swarm for good, and it =
looks like Sacca is doing the same. What about web3?</p><h3 style=3D"-moz-o=
